# Schulz Döner Control — frontend environment
# Copy to `.env.local` for local overrides (git-ignored) or set in the build pipeline.

# Base URL the SPA prefixes onto every /api/... call.
#
# - Same-origin deployment (SPA served from the same host as the API): leave EMPTY
#   or unset → calls use relative paths (e.g. /api/auth/me).
# - Separate-origin deployment (SPA on app.* , API on api.*): set this to the API
#   origin, e.g. https://api.example.com. A trailing slash is trimmed automatically,
#   so callers always pass a leading-slash path.
#
# Cookie auth (httpOnly dc_access/dc_refresh) + the dc_xsrf double-submit token work
# cross-origin because the apiClient sends `credentials: "include"` and echoes the
# `X-XSRF-TOKEN` header; the API must answer with `Access-Control-Allow-Credentials`
# and list this SPA's origin in `Auth:AllowedOrigins`.
VITE_API_BASE=
